Files:
- plugins/excel-online/src/tools/evaluate-formula.ts (add try/finally)

Context:
The handle function performs three sequential API calls (lines 28-43):
```typescript
// Write formula
await workbookApi(`/worksheets('${ws}')/range(address='${tempCell}')`, {
  method: 'PATCH',
  body: { formulas: [[params.formula]] },
});

// Read result
const result = await workbookApi<{...}>(`/worksheets('${ws}')/range(address='${tempCell}')`);

// Clear
await workbookApi(`/worksheets('${ws}')/range(address='${tempCell}')/clear`, {
  method: 'POST',
  body: { applyTo: 'All' },
});
```

If the read on line 34 throws (network timeout, API error), the clear on line 40 never runs. The formula remains in the user's workbook.

Fix: Wrap the read and result-building in a try block, with the clear in a finally block:
```typescript
await workbookApi(/* write formula */);

let result;
try {
  result = await workbookApi<{...}>(/* read result */);
} finally {
  await workbookApi(/* clear */).catch(() => {});
}
```

The `.catch(() => {})` on the clear prevents a double-throw if both read and clear fail.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the workbookApi function
- The temp cell address ZZ9999 is fine — don't change it
- Keep the existing result extraction logic after the try/finally
